This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-categories, as it deals with the bias in vision-language tasks and proposes a framework for image captioning. The use of causal inference principles also suggests a potential overlap with machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the mention of the MS-COCO dataset may indicate a connection to computer vision and pattern recognition (cs.CR) sub-category.
